      Publication ancrée
      Nico Söllinger
      9 novembre 2013 · Erfurt

      ..:: To all our new members, please READ THIS very carefully ::..
      At first welcome here and enjoy your stay. Feel free to ask your questions, start discussions (in the range of the group rules/netiquette of course),
      share your tutorials and source codes. We've got a lot of very good and creative developers in our group that gonna try to help you with your coding
      problems or what ever. The language of this group is English.
      :: BEFORE you asks about any Tutorial please take a... look in our Files-Section (the Tab below the group-header) AND/OR ask Dr. Google!
      :: NO there doesn't exist the best Tutorial for C#, you have to figure it out for your self. Everyone learns in different ways, and so the requirements are different too.
      :: IF you like to post some Code, PLEASE use pastebin.com or similar services if your code/snippet is longer than 5 lines (no one likes Spaghetti-Code)
      :: NO we don't do your Homeworks! You could ask for help about specific tasks, but not for whole projects (until you don't like to pay us for that)!
      :: NO Advertising! Job postings, or postings about "We build your Website/Software/Genome", also non-cost free Tutorials/Trainings aren't allowed, and could resulting in a permanently ban!

      greetz, me -> nico
